                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1177" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1177" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1177" type="surname" value="WESTAWAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1177" type="given" value="EDWIN"></interp>EDWIN WESTAWAY</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with my father, John Westaway, in Gower-street North—he is a watch-maker. On Thursday night, the 24th of Ja<lb></lb>nuary, I was in the parlour, and saw somebody stepping out of the shop—I told my brother, and he went out.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1178" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1178" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1178" type="surname" value="WESTAWAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1178" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY WESTAWAY</persName>
                  </hi>. I was told of this by my brother, and missed a time-piece from a stand in front of the shop, near the door—I saw the prisoner go off the step of the door, and throw the time-piece against the chapel—I pursued, and took him—I had not lost sight of him at all.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> When he overtook me in Euston-square, he said, "Tell me where the property is, and I will not prosecute you." <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> No, I did not—when I took him, he said, "Pray don't—pray don't"—I said, "Pray don't what?" and the officer came and took him.</p>
               <p>
